==English==
===Noun===
# The flowing out and in of the tide.
#''(figurative)'' A large flowing out and in.

====Quotations====
*'''1998''': Slumbering with the '''ebb and the flow''' of this foaming tomb &mdash; Tuomas Holopainen, ''The Pharaoh Sails To Orion'', ''Oceanborn album'', 1998
*'''2001''': I want to hear the roaring '''ebb and flow''' of Broadway &mdash; ''The New Yorker Online'', 29 Oct 2001

